or or other factors;‚Ä¢reduced earnings due to larger credit losses because our loans are concentrated by loan type, industry segment, borrower type, or location of the borrower or collateral;‚Ä¢the rate of delinquencies and amount of loans charged-off;‚Ä¢the adequacy of the level of our allowance for loan losses and the amount of loan loss provisions required in future periods;‚Ä¢costs or difficulties related to the integration of the banks we acquired or may acquire, including vantagesouth bank, may be greater than expected;‚Ä¢results of examinations by our regulatory authorities, including the possibility that the regulatory authorities may, among other things, require us to increase our allowance for loan losses or writedown assets;‚Ä¢the amount of our loan portfolio collateralized by real estate, and the weakness in the commercial real estate market;‚Ä¢our ability to maintain appropriate levels of capital, including levels of capital required under the capital rules implementing basel iii;‚Ä¢the impact of our efforts to raise capital on our financial position, liquidity, capital, and profitability;‚Ä¢the increase in the cost of capital of our series t and series t-acb preferred stock in 2014 if we do not redeem within five years of the date of issuance;‚Ä¢adverse changes in asset quality and resulting credit risk-related losses and expenses;‚Ä¢increased funding costs due to market illiquidity, increased competition for funding, and increased regulatory requirements with regard to funding;‚Ä¢significant increases in competitive pressure in the banking and financial services industries;‚Ä¢changes in the interest rate environment which could reduce anticipated or actual margins;‚Ä¢changes in political conditions or the legislative or regulatory environment, including the effect of recent financial reform legislation on the banking industry;‚Ä¢general economic conditions, either nationally or regionally and especially in our primary service area, becoming less favo